      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELLI JOH (3) was well fancied last start but had to work when racing parked and felt the pinch late. She is better than that and won the only time she attempted this circuit and distance. Draws well so worth another chance. MIKI MARK (8) is a consistent gelding who has placed in five of his last six outings, coming from this barrier for a 3.3m third here last week. Should enjoy a soft run and is a chance to break through. SHEZABLUECHIP (5) has had five weeks off since a last-start fourth here. Draws wider but also comes back in grade. OLLY ODD POTTS (6) draws wide but there was merit in the latest effort when beaten 3.6m into fourth at Shepparton. BLUE OCEAN (2) draws for another good showing.",
